	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Illusive</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">September 12th, 2007 03:59 PM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>Fix/wish list</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>Lets start a new bug / fixes list the one from xara was out-dated and a lot of the stuff in that post has been addressed or is working as intended.<br />
<br />
I hear dev's are doing a quick fix pass(non code related fixes) slated for GU3 so lets see if we can complie a list of stuff and I'll send a pm over to talisker and aviar on the soe forums with the completed list, and hope for the best.  At least its &quot;somthing&quot; more than what we have now which is nothing.<br />
<br />
<br />
<u>Chromantic Halo</u><br />
***edit*** My toon was bugged, Learning this ability is working fine.<br />
However the description on the mobs still says +50% spell reduction, and they take just that 50% less spell damage with the buff up.  <br />
<br />
<u>Finishers</u><br />
When using flamespear our 1st and 2nd fire finisher will not activate if past 30m range.  only our 1st and 2nd cold finishers will light up and be usable.<br />
<br />
<u>Z axis bugs with Conical abilities</u><br />
Color spray &amp; 1st/2nd cold finishers.<br />
If you are on un'even terrain you have to pan your camera up / down via PgUp and PgDn keys so that you can hit your target if standing above / below them, and if you dont hit the mob due to Z axis the refresh timer is incurred.<br />
<br />
<u>Seradon's falling star</u><br />
The ability is very underpowered.  The cast time is just too long for the damage it deals.  It needs a significant damage boost or cast time reduction.  many have been asking for this to be our large single target nuke.  If possible up the damage and remove the chance to root.<br />
<br />
<u>taqmir's barrage</u><br />
This ability needs a minor tweak, a damage boost/higher crit bonus or cast time reduction will go a long way to making it more used ability.<br />
<br />
<u>Chaos volley</u><br />
still get epic / legendary self feedback damage from this, and we still get feedback damage when it is resisted.<br />
We can get partial resists on the feedback damage inflicted to us be never a full resist unless we use our arcane immunity self buff.<br />
<br />
<u>Energy shards</u><br />
There is a bug in that if you cast an energy shard while wearing a Quicksilver ring, and log out(for an extended period of time) while the refresh timer is counting down, when you log back in you will have the full 1 hour recast restriction placed on it.<br />
If you log out right after the refresh timer expires at the 45m mark (with quick silver ring) and come back in say the next day you will incur the 1 hour recast restriction.  <br />
You must wait the full hour after casting the shard, or when you log back in you will have the 1 hour recast lockout.<br />
<br />
<u>Energy rift</u><br />
This ability does not scale very well at higher levels.  its power cost is very high, when coupled with the high endurance cost. Currently its more efficient to use fireball for more damage and less power and less endurance.  Can the endurance or energy cost get re-evaluated and reduced on higher lvl versions?<br />
<br />
<u>icequake</u><br />
The scaling on this spell is non existant.  it has the same snare duration as the first version, and there is zero reason to use the highest lvl version.  The power cost on this ability is also very high, and needs a reduction.<br />
<br />
<u>Mantle of ether</u><br />
This dropped group lvl 50 spell has the same arcane resistance (270) as the single target arcane debuff we get at lvl 50.  It needs a slight upgrade.  <br />
<br />
<u>Firebarrier 3</u><br />
The scaling on firebarrier 1 and 2 are very good.  The scaling on the &quot;energy regeneration&quot; from firebarrier 2 to firebarrier 3 is very poor.  it goes from 22 per 6s to 26 per 6s. or a net gain of 4 energy per 6s.  Can this get looked into and increased if neccessary?<br />
<br />
<u>Disperse / reflect group wards</u><br />
counterspelling with disperse/reflect will still sometimes drop the ward from all group members.  For example if you have both wards up and the mob casts a spell you disperse it, the log will indicate each member of the party dispersed the spell and the spell ward is removed from each of them.  The same holds true for reflect.<br />
I know a few have asked to have back the single target version of this spell, a single target 3.0s cast while keeping the group 6.0s cast.  Is this feasable?<br />
<br />
<u>Char</u><br />
This spell needs a small damage increase and could use it by increasing the number of dot ticks by an additional 6 seconds for a total of 10s or 5 dot ticks 1 per 2s.<br />
<br />
<u>Forget</u><br />
This spell still does not appear to be reducing hate other than the 2.0s of cast time of not dealing damage.<br />
<br />
<u>Magic Immunity Self Buffs (sanctuary lines)</u><br />
Ethereal sanctuary - the +300 to arcane resistance after the 15second immunity wears off does not stack with our self arcane buff.  At lvl 50 we can self buff 270 to arcane, this barrier gives us only +30 since it does not stack.  We think they should stack.<br />
The rest- We would like to see each one on a separate timer and not linked.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
