		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Chromatic Halo <br />
- agreed<br />
<br />
Finishers <br />
- agreed. Noticed this as well, I doubt it's working as intended (tm) so a fix would be nice.<br />
<br />
Z axis bugs with Conical abilities - <br />
hmm havn't really noticed this but I don't doubt its there, also not sure these conical abilities are supposed/intended to spread in the Z axis?<br />
<br />
Seradon's falling star <br />
agreed that it's underpowered. But if you want to up the damage and remove chance to root you basically have another Flamespear but with shorter range. No real need for this. <br />
I'm not sure why we got this spell in the first place, it doesn't really bring much new or flavor to the table. My suggestion would be to remove this spell and replace it with a longer (minute long) DoT spelline. Not asking for something as good as the more dot-based casters got, but a small longlasting DoT would be cool. <br />
<br />
taqmir's barrage<br />
I'm not sure I agree on this one. Its pretty much only asking to make the class more powerful, and this spell has its uses. I'm sure you noticed in groups with the right buffs its possible to get the casttime on this very fast.<br />
<br />
Chaos volley<br />
I agree on the crit feedback on this spell, this should be removed. But I don't understand why we shouldn't get feedback if the mob resists the spell? That's something the mob does, and shouldn't affect its feedback. Just remove the chance of crit on the feedback and this would be enough.<br />
<br />
Energy shards <br />
Yes, please have a look at this. Annoying bug.<br />
<br />
Energy rift<br />
Agree somewhat, the last version need damage upped a little to be worth using. But I like the endurance cost, its adds a demand for at least one item with +end regen (which helps a ton). You know you can put resonating crystals of recovery on more than chest, as description says. Get situational AE gear and you'll notice big difference!<br />
<br />
icequake<br />
Agree somewhat, maybe we don't need as many versions of this spell? Agree the energy cost is a bit high, but I love the no-limit (that I've noticed) to how many mobs it can affect (unlike in EQ where it was 4). Nothing like the rush of pulling 9 (my record so far) mobs with it and go at them with fireball, to be totally out of energy when they all drop :)<br />
<br />
Mantle of ether <br />
- agree, a little bonus would be in order<br />
<br />
Firebarrier 3<br />
Maybe a few points more on it, but again if you increase this too much there would be less demand for +energy regen on gear. Gearing up should be about having to make choices, sacrificing one thing to gain another. When you power-up abilities it calls for a look on other classes, and you're back on sqare one balance wise.<br />
<br />
Disperse / reflect group wards <br />
- Agree, gief self only version.<br />
<br />
Char<br />
Nah, see previons comments about increasing abilities, also my suggestion for a longer lasting dot instead of S falling star could help with this.<br />
<br />
Forget <br />
- Agree, and this is one of my major concerns. Please have a look at this spell. It can't be working as intended (tm).<br />
<br />
Magic Immunity Self Buffs (sanctuary lines)<br />
Don't really agree, having them on separate timers may be too powerful for the PvPers, maybe also in PvE, but I have to admit I havn't played much with these spells other than the first one for CV feedback..</div>
	</td>
</tr>
