<br />
3. My experiences with the wards are good when it comes to grouping: as soon as everyone is there, i cast the two barriers and chromatic halo with a precedent amplify effectivity. Once i get the mobs turning to me, this gives the tank a few seconds to regain aggro, the healer to switch to me and me some time to fully burn the mob or deaggro ;) If you have an eye on your aggro you should be able to recast all the wards again after the fight.<br />
On the other hand, all the wards are useless while soloing, cause if you're fighting a caster mob, its either a 2/3dot which you should be able to burn anyway or a 4dot+ which takes too long to kill to keep your wards up during the fight.</div>
