		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>Ok since we are talking about &quot;fixes&quot; ....<br />
<br />
I am lucky enough to do some testing in APW and i have some dreadfull news :<br />
<b><font color="Red">Wards Dismiss/Counterspell seems to be useless vs Bosses.</font></b><br />
<br />
Now of course this is not a surprise to anyone, and as i have already said many many<br />
times, if you expected yourself to rune out of a Dragons AE or Dismiss a God you are naive.<br />
<br />
<br />
Since Grimoire is MIA, and Cylus will be gone soon, something has to be done.<br />
I will be sending an email to someone in SoE to talk to him about a huge part<br />
of our class that will become useless with raids..<br />
<br />
This is the email, please feel free to add any ideas suggestions :<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2">
			<hr />
			
				The sorcerer class is build around 2 core ideas : DPS + Caster Disruption.<br />
This is why we have skills as Nulling/Reflective Wards and Reflect/Dismiss<br />
<br />
<br />
<b><font color="red">A) Spell Runes</font></b><br />
<br />
For a long long time, sorcerers used to have 2 spell runes/wards.<br />
Nulling Ward &amp; Reflective Ward.<br />
<br />
These were single target wards that either &quot;nulled&quot; or &quot;reflected&quot; a spell.<br />
I do not remember the manacost, but the casting time was 3.0 seconds.<br />
<br />
You could &quot;prebuff&quot; the entire group, and thus protect them from 2 spells.<br />
But it would take 24 to 36 seconds to do that.<br />
<br />
At some point, the wards were changed in theory for the better.<br />
They became &quot;Group Nulling Ward&quot; and &quot;Group Reflective Ward&quot; <br />
with a casting time of 6.0 seconds. <br />
<br />
Which means that with the adequate setup, a sorcerer can do a FULL group<br />
Warding every 3 seconds. <br />
 <br />
Quite Obviously, this just killed all the AEs in the game.<br />
(This was already a very overpowered for single group content, <br />
but vs a Dragon 4 sorcerer in 4 groups = AE totally negated). <br />
<br />
All the mobs we tested yesturday ignored my runes.<br />
The &quot;Curse Guy&quot; has a DoT and a Curse, both which ignored my runes<br />
The &quot;2 Adds Guy&quot; has an AE Stun, which ignored my runes <br />
I did not see any spells for X99, but they will probably be ignored too.<br />
<br />
<br />
This point is very important, because it is with fire/cold/arcane resist<br />
the only buffs a sorcerer has to help a group. We help fight casters.<br />
<br />
 <br />
<br />
<b><font color="Red">B) Dismiss/Reflect</font></b><br />
<br />
These two skills are also related to &quot;caster fighting&quot;.<br />
As their name implies they are used to fight casters.<br />
<br />
They work like &quot;Counterspell and Reflect&quot; in Magic the Gathering.<br />
Any spell cast by your target, can be either dismissed, or reflected back to him.<br />
<br />
Again, for all raid mobs we tested yesturday, my Dismiss/Reflect were ignored.<br />
<br />
 <br />
<br />
While it is worth noting that both Wards/Dismiss have been acting unreliably (fubar)<br />
since beta (every sorcerer will tell you they are half bugged), it is clear that <br />
you will have to be na&#239;ve to expect 1 person to be able to &quot;shut down&quot; a dragon.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
<b><font color="red">C) Conclusion &amp; Solutions</font></b><br />
<br />
While i am really greatfull towards the person that came up with the idea<br />
it lacks some insight for &quot;real life application&quot;.<br />
 <br />
To be honest, i do not see any solution regarding these skills for a Sorcerer <br />
(at least under their current version).<br />
 <br />
If they are made operationnal in raids, they are very very very overpowered.<br />
And if you make events tuned around them, 4 sorcerer will be mandatory for<br />
maximum Warding speed in every event with AE. <br />
It is the same problem EQ had with &quot;stun&quot;.<br />
<br />
<br />
You can probably add gimmick spells/AEs on trash to make<br />
sorcerer secondary function (caster disruptor) usefull, but i dont like gimmicks.<br />
(See Hunter Tranquil Shot in WoW). <br />
This does not help my class, or balance the fact Wards/Dismiss are overpowered.<br />
<br />
 <br />
<font color="Lime"><b>D) The only solution would be a change to the Mechanics of the class.</b></font><br />
<br />
You are not the &quot;Sorcerer&quot; dev, so asking for &quot;class chances&quot; is a long shot.<br />
However, i hope that you may be able to transfer my mail to someone that can look<br />
into this issue, because it is more of a class problem than raid problem. <br />
<br />
What do i propose ?<br />
<br />
Delete Nulling Ward<br />
-&gt; Replace it by a &quot;Single Target Rune Ward&quot; that eats spell damage <br />
   The damage absorbed increases with level (exactly like spellshield).<br />
   Making sure Chaos Volley feedback is ignored by this ward. <br />
   Slow enough be useless for in fight group buffing but fast enough to be usable.<br />
   (Like when we had Wizards do Spellshield rotation in PoTime for Tallon Zek Procs)<br />
<br />
Delete Reflecting Ward<br />
-&gt; Replace it by a &quot;Self Only Rune&quot; <br />
   A copy of the Clicky on : <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3719" target="_blank">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3719</a><br />
   That will help sorcerers be less fragile, and more enduring.<br />
   Making sure Chaos Volley feedback is ignored by this ward.<br />
<br />
Add A Counterspell : Sorcerer's Discretion<br />
-&gt; Aggro will probably be a huge problem in raids. <br />
   Specially because of the 15% miss rate vs lvl53 mobs with full defensive tanks.<br />
   Since we cant expect to Dismiss/Reflect spell cast by bosses, this will help. <br />
   What should it do ? : Channels a bit of the Residual energy left <br />
by your target's spell to reduce your hate by X% for 10 seconds.<br />
<br />
I do agree that my changes will weaken our class (specially in AE debuff heavy zones),<br />
But if we do not have overpowered abilities, encounters can be tuned easily.<br />
<br />
<br />
Xennumet with a sorcerer is trivial (since silence will almost never land on anyone).<br />
Without a sorcerer its really really tricky (25 sec silence = dead group).<br />
<br />
<br />
Best Regards<br />
<br />
			
			<hr />
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div>
<br />
<br />
Lets face it, 3.0 Second (fully hasted) group Wards are OVERPOWERED.<br />
So we either get them changed/nerfed, or they will be at best situationnal.<br />
The same for Dismiss/Reflect.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
